text: These are the letters which Endymion wrote%% To one he loved in secret and apart,

And now the brawlers of the auction-mart%% Bargain and bid for each poor blotted note,
Bargain and bid for each poor blotted note,&& Aye! for each separate pulse of passion quote
Aye! for each separate pulse of passion quote%% The merchant's price! I think they love not art
The merchant's price! I think they love not art%% Who break the crystal of a poet's heart,
Who break the crystal of a poet's heart,&& That small and sickly eyes may glare or gloat.
That small and sickly eyes may glare or gloat.&& Is it not said, that many years ago,
Is it not said, that many years ago,&& In a far Eastern town some soldiers ran
In a far Eastern town some soldiers ran%% With torches through the midnight, and began
With torches through the midnight, and began%% To wrangle for mean raiment, and to throw
To wrangle for mean raiment, and to throw%% Dice for the garments of a wretched man,
Dice for the garments of a wretched man,&& Not knowing the God's wonder, or his woe?
